derivation.yuyuan_name: late Middle English: from Latin nominativus 'relating to naming', translation of Greek onomastikē (ptōsis) 'naming (case')

entry.def: In the grammar of some languages, the nominative or the nominative case is the case used for a noun when it is the subject of a verb.

means.word_mean: 1. the category of nouns serving as the grammatical subject of a verb
1. serving as or indicating the subject of a verb and words identified with the subject of a copular verb;
2. named; bearing the name of a specific person;
